---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const title = "Q1 Goals Bingo: Staying Intentional Through a Seattle Winter";
export const date = "2026-02-25";
export const excerpt =
  "Seattle winters can turn into inertia fast. So I made a bingo board — not productivity bingo, joy bingo — and started treating the grey as an invitation.";
export const tags = ["seattle", "intentional-living", "q1-2026"];
---

<SiteLayout title={`${title} — Saachi K Gupta`}>
  <h1>{title}</h1>
  <p style="opacity:0.7;">{date}</p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    I love living in Washington. I love that I can be on a ferry, skiing, swimming in the lake, or at a concert within the same day.
  </p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    But winter here can be hard, especially when ski season is....tepid. 
  </p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    So instead of letting winter happen to me, I made a bingo board to set a vision for my winter.
  </p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    Not productivity bingo. Not "optimize my life" bingo. Joy bingo.
  </p>

  <figure>
    <img src="/images/bingo.jpeg" alt="Handwritten 2026 bingo board with squares for skiing, swimming, biking, parks, and Seattle adventures" />
    <figcaption>The 2026 board. Diagonal lines mean a bingo. Tally marks are for the squares I keep coming back to — tracking consistency, not just completion.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2 style="margin-top: 28px;">The Q1 Bingo Board</h2>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">Some squares are small:</p>
  <ul style="max-width: 75ch;">
    <li>Walk a new pocket park</li>
    <li>Try a coffee shop I've never been to</li>
    <li>Host a Sunday soup night</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">Some are slightly bigger:</p>
  <ul style="max-width: 75ch;">
    <li>Ferry day trip with friends</li>
    <li>Cold plunge and sauna</li>
    <li>Bike somewhere I'd normally drive</li>
    <li>Go to a weekday workout class</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">Some are about connection:</p>
  <ul style="max-width: 75ch;">
    <li>Plan a themed dinner</li>
    <li>Invite someone new into an existing friend group</li>
    <li>Send the "we should hang" text and actually set the date</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    The goal isn't to win. It's to stay engaged. Winter can shrink your world if you let it. Bingo expands mine.
  </p>

  <h2 style="margin-top: 28px;">What I'm Noticing</h2>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    Beyond the bingo board, I've started listing the hyper-specific things that make living here feel special — not the postcard moments, the small ones.
  </p>

  <ul style="max-width: 75ch;">
    <li>Ferry rides with no destination</li>
    <li>Rainy walks around Capitol Hill</li>
    <li>Watching storms roll over Lake Washington</li>
    <li>Swimming at Madison Park when it finally warms up</li>
    <li>Taking the long way home along the water</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    These are the things that remind me: I chose to live here. I love living here. Winter is still part of the story.
  </p>

  <h2 style="margin-top: 28px;">Healthier Ways to Hang Out</h2>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">Winter used to default to drinking, complaining about the weather, and talking about when it would be summer again.</p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">Now I try to default to:</p>
  <ul style="max-width: 75ch;">
    <li>Walk and talk instead of sit and drink</li>
    <li>Workout class followed by coffee</li>
    <li>Ferry and journaling</li>
    <li>Soup night instead of bar night</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    Not because I'm anti-fun. Because I want my social life to add energy, not drain it.
  </p>

  <h2 style="margin-top: 28px;">Why This Matters</h2>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    Small intentional rituals change momentum. When it's grey for weeks, it's easy to feel stalled. But the bingo board is a reminder: I don't need perfect bluebird ski days to love this place. I need movement, light, water, and people.
  </p>

  <p style="max-width: 75ch;">
    This isn't about achievement. It's about agency.
  </p>
</SiteLayout>
